  "id": "019cdcdc-fd00-7850-9bc2-a8c40a647dbb",
  "content": "# M3.3: Embedding & Chunking Strategy Implementation Plan\n\n> **For Claude:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task.\n\n**Goal:** Build a trait-based chunking framework with five format strategies, a kernel orchestrator pipeline, and revised ingestion flow — completing D65-D69.\n\n**Architecture:** `ChunkingPipeline` orchestrates format routing via `FormatRegistry`, delegating to `ChunkingStrategy` implementations (FallbackChunker, MarkdownChunker, ConfigChunker, PdfChunker, AstChunker). The `IngestionAdapter` trait is revised per D69 to return raw `SourceFile`s instead of `KnowledgeEntry`s. The pipeline handles universal concerns: merge small → enforce budget → split oversized → overlap context.\n\n**Tech Stack:** Rust (edition 2024), tree-sitter (AST), pdf-extract (PDF text), existing corvia-kernel token_estimator + chunking_strategy types.\n\n---\n",
